Technical Notes
• The trend line is a smoothed conditional mean, specifically a Locally Estimated Scatterplot Smoother (or LOESS).
• Wastewater Viral Activity levels are based on the CDC methodology linked below, with two differences: (1) use of weighted statistics (median and standard deviation) to calculate thresholds, with population served and reporting interval as weights; and (2) The baseline is updated each time the WVA is calculated, rather than every 6 months.
• All analysis and visualization is performed in R. Data and scripts are accessible in the github respository here: [https://github.com/raughter/western-mass-covid].

Data Sources
• CDC methodology: https://www.cdc.gov/nwss/about-data.html#data-method
• Wastewater data access: https://www.mass.gov/info-details/wastewater-surveillance-reporting
• Population weights are from various sources (EPA estimates whenever available).
